  "text": "The requirements of older people using public transport have previously been studied by considering them in groups with particular characteristics. [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] distinguished older people in different age intervals and explored the needs for each of those intervals. In the Euro Access project, a differentiation was made based on the impairments of older people: Mobility impairments, visual impairments, hearing impairments and cognitive impairments. Apart from the user perspective, the needs of older people could be explored from a system perspective (i.e. what are the characteristics of a system suitable for older people).",
